rComments: There is a significant amount of work you have to do: readings, participation (where you have to refer back to the readings and textbook in order to get the marks), assignments, paper and facilitating a seminar. The course material is interesting yet a bit daunting to learn at times. She is a knowledgable prof, yet I found her to be intimidating.

For a 400 level course she gave 3 essays (one which was 12 pages), that were only worth 10-15%, a 3 hour seminar presentation worth 10%, an exam worth 30%, AND participation in which you must refer to the textbook or readings if you want a decent grade. Extremely picky when marking, and often talks to fast. She is very smart in he field though.
Professor Gibbs is really nice and there are no surprises on her exams
She was an amazing prof! Best in university!
Professor Gibbs is an excellent professor. She is smart and her instructions for assignments are crystal clear. She doesn't pull any punches and has a straightforward marking style

Yawn.  On the midterm/final she says no 'wikipedia' answers for short answer questions.  That's bull! List everything and anything related to your question and fill up your page with wikipedia answers!
extremely helpful to students. She's very articulate but talks quite fast. I've learned a lot from her.

I've taken almost all of her courses since my first year. If you have no interset in Poli Sci, her classes are not for you as they will not pique your interest. She is very smart and knows her stuff but should slow down when speaking or put more info in her slides.

In addition, the related questions of Part II of mid term or final exam are also to be answered in the little space provided, which is not always easy to do. Other than this, she is a fantastic person and Professor, in my modest opinion.

Great teacher! However, please beware of her mid term and final exam format because she gives little space for us to write definitions of various terms in Part I, which can be problematic for students who have the tendency to write a lot of details and in long essay style.  In addition, the related questions of Part II of mid term or final exam a
Great teacher with lots of enthusiasm, but tends to talk really fast. Although the course material was rather dry she kept it interesting with relative fun facts.

shes nice and all but talks waaaaay too fast to be able to copy down lecture notes... eventually u realize that shes just practically reading the textbook sooo... no point of attendance or even bothering to keep up with her, just read the textbook

For a 4th year course, she is hopeless. About 20 people in the class and a seminar format but she would be the one doing the talking. She expects us to discuss, facilitate the discussion but ends up doing it anyway...and she marks us on this every week!! What kind of strategy is that? She was all very nice at the end bcoz we were doing evaluations.
Amazing professor. Her intelligence is obvious, and despite boring material, made this class my favourite.
She taught me canadian politics.... boring, and focuses too much on details that add nothing to your pol sci education. No emphasis whatsoever on perspective... dryest course EVER!

Incomprehensible, her high level jargon is just over the top..either she is a show off or doesntknow anything. Not helpful with personal circumstances..so dontbother plus she loves talking but wants studentsto discuss her lecture style is useless and she isnot considerate of student lives with her 5-7 readings per week course syllabus

Stick to the required readings and don't goto class. No structure in her class. Her 1hr lecture/1hr seminar structure isn't good. Most of the time its the same 5 ppl talking for an hour. That hour is best spent doing the readings. Exams aren't that hard if you do the readings but BEWARE of the essay.... gl trying to find a essay question
